title.narrative: SOUTH ASIA REGIONAL TRADE AND INTEGRATION PROGRAMME (SARTIP) - WORLD BANK SUPPORT

description.narrative: This activity (SOUTH ASIA REGIONAL TRADE AND INTEGRATION PROGRAMME (SARTIP) - WORLD BANK SUPPORT) is a component of SOUTH ASIA REGIONAL TRADE AND INTEGRATION PROGRAMME reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Multilateral organisation' and a budget of £16,765,831. This component benefits Asia, regional, and works in the following sector(s): Trade policy and administrative management, Trade facilitation, Regional trade agreements (RTAs). , with the following implementing partners: DAI Europe, IMC Worldwide, International Bank for Reconstruction and Development (IBRD), United Nations Economic and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific (ESCAP). The start date is 27-02-2012 and the end date is 31-03-2018.
